column1: # Began survey at 10:30 and ended by 14:50.  At beginning, there was 100% cloud cover (not really cold though), and at 13:30 the sun came out.

# based on survey, Calop_pre_tentmines are not visible from the top of the leaf and may be too hard to consistently survey.  Same thing may be true for damage that usually occurs along the midvein of the leaf

# I'm worried that the same Caloptilia pruniella larva could make multiple LTFs, if it is on a plant in poor condition that has small leafs.  Therefore, I think I should only use Calop_tent_mine as representatives of their abundance.
# Need to trim Carex sp. (slough sedge) in plots.  Also, Site 2's Unexposed plants don't appear to have the best wind break
